Chapter 7: Ready And Willing <br>
With the new FMS tested and proven, Harper brought the Maru back aboard the Andromeda. He left the ship the second it was docked with a celebratory Sparky in hand. Harper ran straight to Machine Shop Twelve to check on production. Just as he left the hanger he bumped into Dylan. <br>
<br>
“Harper slow down.” He yelled. <br>
<br>
“Sorry Dylan gotta check up on the production line.” <br>
<br>
“Ok, but slow down.” Harper started running. “And Harper.” <br>
<br>
“Yeah?” <br>
<br>
“Good job.” <br>
<br>
“Thanks.” And he hurried away before Dylan came up with something else for him to do. <br>
<br>
About an hour later all the FMS production was complete and Rommie’s bots were loading them into the Maru as Harper installed one on the Andromeda. With the loading and installation complete Harper and Rommie left in the Maru to install a modified FMS on every ship in the fleet, at Dylan’s request of course. With a fleet of 67 other ships that was no small task but Dylan insisted that Harper oversee the installation throughout the entire fleet since he had the most experience, even if it did take the rest of the day, which it did. The Maru returned shortly after midnight, and, for once Harper went straight to bed. <br>
<br>
This action alone had Rommie very, very worried, as it also did Trance. She too had been up late jut making sure that each hip had plenty of supplies. She turned the corner as Harper left the hanger bay: stumbling as he did, she had never seen him so tired. Trance ran over and helped him up, she wanted to take him to medical to check him out but as soon as he was up Harper started walking towards his quarters. Trance followed him a few metres behind, just in case. Once Harper was safely inside she called to Andromeda. <br>
<br>
“Andromeda, keep an eye on Harper will you?” <br>
<br>
“I’m afraid he just engaged privacy mode Trance. I…” She was cut off. <br>
<br>
“Medical over ride, disengage privacy mode, authorisation Trance Gemini Chief Medical Officer – Lambda Red 3981…” She paused. “Lambda Red 3981 Harper.” <br>
<br>
Andromeda hesitated. “Unusual code, but valid, I’ll let you know if anything happens.” <br>
<br>
“Thank you.” Trance hated herself for what she’d just done, and for what she just gave away, but it was for Harper’s own good. She worried about him, more than either of them knew. She knew deep down that she had shown Andromeda a side of herself, a secret, she would rather not have, but she also knew Andromeda and was sure that it would not go any further. <br>
<br>
Andromeda’s hologram materialised several hours later in Trances quarters at the foot of the bed. Slowly the lights came on and built up to a level sufficient to wake Trance. Aside from the young woman, Andromeda was the only other person aboard to see inside her quarters. Trance awoke almost immediately. <br>
<br>
“Harper!” She almost yelled. <br>
<br>
“His heart rate has rapidly increased and his breathing become very erratic, his temperature also increased by three degrees Centigrade and his body keeps flailing and squirming. It’s most likely a nightmare but I thought you should know.” <br>
<br>
“Thanks.” Said Trance as she sprinted out of the room towards Harper’s. <br>
<br>
As soon as Trance reached the door Andromeda opened it for her. Trance rushed inside straight to Harper’s bedside. She began to shake him vigorously to try and wake him. When that failed Andromeda turned the lights up full which. For a moment blinded Trance, even she couldn’t go from dim to star strength that fast. However, even such a strong light failed to wake Harper up. When he wouldn’t wake Trance and Andromeda became very worried. <br>
<br>
Before calling Beka or Dylan, Trance wanted to try one last thing. She placed her hand on Harper’s forehead to steady it, and then slowly she bent forward and gently kissed Harper’s right cheek. His skin was soft and moist against her lips due to the sweat, not like when she was purple – before the switch – but it was enough. Harper slowly began to rouse from his slumber; the first thing he saw brought warm feelings to his heart. By this time, Andromeda had turned the lights down to what they were when Trance first came in. As Harper looked up at Trance’s face he stared into her eyes and he could swear he saw dozens of galaxies. After staring for what seemed like an eternity Harper came back to reality. <br>
<br>
He sat up in bed and looked at Trance soon realising that she was wearing only a nightgown and robe but, for some reason that eluded him at the time, that wasn’t what he was looking at. Here he was in his quarters with this beautiful woman barely dressed in a silk nightgown and robe and he wasn’t even looking at her but at the space around her that drew his attention. Harper could swear that Trance was radiation a golden glow lighting the space around her – not much, it probably wouldn’t have been visible during the day but now, in the dim light of his quarters it was very, very clear. Harper couldn’t believe it, he was in aw, as he stared at Trance he suddenly realised that she was speaking and that he hadn’t heard a word. <br>
<br>
“Trance, Trance what is it?” <br>
<br>
“I said are you alright? Andromeda told me that you’re heart rate and breathing were unstable. She was worried about you.” <br>
<br>
“Yeah, yeah I’m fine Trance, thanks.” <br>
<br>
“You don’t look fine, that must have been some nightmare, trying to wake you was really difficult, and, according to the super genius that is you, you’re a very light sleeper, after growing up on Earth.” <br>
<br>
“Well, it was pretty bad.” <br>
<br>
Trance looked at her friend, her compassion showing in her eyes. <br>
<br>
“Do you wanna talk about it? You really should you know.” <br>
<br>
“Trance babe, as much as I hate to disappoint, especially you, this really isn’t the kind of thing you and I ‘can’ talk about.” How could they talk about it – after all, the dream was about her, for the most part anyway. <br>
<br>
“Are you sure?” <br>
<br>
“Yeah, I’ll be fine, got a lot to do today anyway, I could use an early start.” <br>
<br>
Trance looked on, her expression hadn’t changed but her compassion had become fear and worry and Harper could see it all too clearly. <br>
<br>
“Tell you what Trance, Andromeda, I want you to keep an eye on me today, ignore any privacy requests and monitor my vitals and all that. If at any time you become concerned for me, inform Trance immediately, got it?” <br>
<br>
“Understood Harper.” <br>
<br>
Trance relaxed, she knew her body was nowhere near as good a liar as she was and it didn’t help when Harper could read her like a book. She knew he’d only done it to calm her down but Trance was glad he did and wouldn’t soon forget Harper’s sacrifice – she knew just how much Harper valued his privacy. Trance rose to leave but he grabbed her hand. <br>
<br>
“Trance, you won’t leave will you?” <br>
<br>
“What do you mean?” <br>
<br>
“Like, you wouldn’t just pack up and go, would you? I mean, well, you know I lost the rest of my family and I feel like you guys are my family now and since I don’t need to worry about you dieing at least, all you can do is leave.” <br>
<br>
“Harper, you don’t have to worry, I’d never leave you like that. Now try to get some sleep, big day, well today, you’ll need it.” Harper lay back down and Trance tucked him in. Just as she was about to leave she bent forward and kissed Harper on the forehead. <br>
<br>
“Sleep tight Seamus.” She left his room and Andromeda turned down the lights. <br>
<br>
“So much for an early start.” He mumbled. <br>
<br>
A few hours later Harper awoke as normal, he got showered, dressed and started the day with his customary can of Sparky. After he was done he headed to the briefing on the Obs deck to find out what Dylan’s master plan was. The briefing wasn’t due to start until 09:00 but Harper got there at 5 to and it was already underway. Dylan however seemed more annoyed at Harper’s presence than his absence. ‘Rommie’ he mumbled, ‘will you ever learn to shut up.’ <br>
<br>
Andromeda’s hologram appeared in miniature form beside him. <br>
<br>
“Actually, I didn’t say a thing. Dylan knew he’d been pushing you really hard lately and he wanted to give you a break, that’s why he started without you and why I didn’t wake you, didn’t you wonder about that – he told me not too.” <br>
<br>
Dylan heard Rommie talking to Harper and looked out to see Harper standing there beside her. Dylan broke from his speech and addressed Harper. <br>
<br>
“Mister Harper, you shouldn’t be here.” <br>
<br>
“Like hell I shouldn’t, Dylan this is my home we’re planning about, I wanna help.” <br>
<br>
“Harper you’ve helped more than enough already, besides, Beka’s going to need you here, just leave this to us. Dismissed.” <br>
<br>
Harper stood his ground for a moment but he couldn’t stand having the Captains of the other ships looking at him like that, even if they were avatars. He slowly started to turn. <br>
<br>
“Fine, but on two conditions.” <br>
<br>
“I’m listening.” Dylan was royally pissed, how dare Harper humiliate him like this, he knew this wasn’t a democracy, he had no right doing this, but, if I would get rid of him…. <br>
<br>
“One, you let me come down the second you win.” <br>
<br>
“Deal, and two?” <br>
<br>
“Stop calling me Mister Harper, its too weird.” <br>
<br>
“Fine. Dismissed.” <br>
<br>
Harper turned as Dylan went back to the briefing, as he walked through the door Harper overheard Dylan detailing some of his plan. <br>
<br>
“The first drop will be at 1400 hours, we estimate all orbital and ninety per cent of all planetary defences will be disabled by then. I’ll lead the first drop, the second will be led by….” Dylan was cut off by the doors closing, but Harper had heard enough, enough to formulate a plan of his own. <br>
