<br>
Dylan sat in his quarters the day after the briefing, the Day Of Liberation as Harper called it; he used the term so much that Dylan had changed the name of the impending attack to Operation Liberty. It was almost noon; he walked towards the closet and removed a combat uniform. He arrived in Command about half an hour later wearing full High Guard battle dress. But this wasn’t just any battle dress, not the basic black uniform with the blue stripe, this was a uniform made especially for his New Commonwealth. It clearly displayed on the collar, in boxes of white rimmed in red the Argosy Special Ops insignia on the right and his rank pin on his left, not to mention the New Commonwealth emblem on the sides of the arms just below the shoulders, the red stripe usually withheld for more formal uniforms adorned this uniform, but rather than coming across the chest and down the wearers right the stripe came across the chest to the right but this time curved down to meet the bottom of the zipper, clasps just didn’t look right, and ran around the bottom just above the waist, and of course, old faithful ever at his side. As Dylan entered Command everyone was present and all eyes were on him, as Rommie looked on Harper looked over towards her, he could swear he saw jealousy on her face, despite having created her and at one point being able to tell what she was thinking from the expression on her face, Rommie had actually grown out of the look she was given and created one of her own, as such Harper could no longer read her like an open book, much to his annoyance. Seeing what he was sure was jealousy he quickly took out a small flexi and handed it to her as he walked by her to get to Dylan, this was his last real chance and he knew it. Just as Harper was about to speak Rommie hurriedly left Command, only Harper knowing why. <br>
<br>
“So how do you like it?” He asked as he approached Dylan at the Captains podium. <br>
<br>
“It’s incredible Mr…” He paused “Harper, sorry.” <br>
<br>
“I’ll let that one slide, this time. You really like it?” Dylan nodded. <br>
<br>
“That’s a relief, I was really getting tired of that black and grew thing you were always wearing, and it was - too plain.” <br>
<br>
“Look Harper, I know why you’re doing this and I can understand why, I would have done anything to save Sara or to reach Tarn Vedra, but the price was too high. Look I can’t even imagine what it was like growing up on Earth but I saw how it effected you, how you reacted when Cuchulain captured us, you were as white as a sheet, you were trembling, you allowed your fear to take over, I need cool heads down there, I’m sorry.” <br>
<br>
“Hey, don’t worry about it, I had to try right.” Harper walked head down shoulders slumped out of Command. Dylan looked around. <br>
<br>
“Anyone else think that was a little too easy?” <br>
<br>
“Yeah definitely.” Beka answered. “No way is it that easy to get rid of Harper, not when he is this personally involved with something, especially his family and believe me, I've tried.” <br>
<br>
“It would appear that the little professor has a plan.” Uttered Tyr. <br>
<br>
“The question is, what is his plan and when is he going to act on it. And how far will he go to see it through to completion.” Trance spoke softly but the worry was very clear in her voice but only she and Rommie and Andromeda knew why. Only the trio knew of Harper’s dreams and only Andromeda knew any details about both, but then, they knew nothing of his second dream, only that it was a terrible nightmare, one which would take him some time to get over, if only he would confide in Rommie, or even Trance; Andromeda knew how Harper felt about the Golden woman even if he didn’t, he might be able to block out the feelings but his body still showed them. <br>
<br>
‘Perhaps he has avoided Trance and focused all of his attention on my avatar for a reason.’ Pondered the Andromeda, she would have to perform some more tests but she thought she had finally figured out the enigma that is Seamus Zelazny Harper. <br>
<br>
As soon as Harper left Command he resumed his natural posture and headed straight for Machine Shop 17. He engaged privacy mode the second he was inside and began a frantic search. The fleet was due to depart and stream to Earth at 13:00 hours and it was already quickly approaching. At about ten to he finally found what he was looking for and set his master plan in motion. <br>
<br>
“I am a genius,” He said to himself, “hell, even Tyr is goinna be proud of this.” <br>
<br>
Back on Command Andromeda gave Dylan the signal; it was time. He took his place at his podium and hailed the fleet. <br>
<br>
“Attention all ships this is Fleet Command, break Battle Group formation and assume Drago Kazov fleet formation, activate the EFMS (Enhanced Footprint Magnification System), bring ECM’s online, activate all weapons and link your NAV systems with the Andromeda’s.” He paused momentarily awaiting acknowledgement from the fleet. <br>
<br>
“All ships report Battle Ready Captain.” Andromeda reported. <br>
<br>
“Lets bring it.” He tuned to Beka. “Beka, if you please.” <br>
<br>
“Transiting to Slipstream in 5, 4, 3, 2, now.” The ship rocked at the initial entry as the tendrils of the stream reached out and pulled the fleet in one by one. <br>
<br>
Beka was glad she only had to do this once, the strain of literally piloting almost 70 ships at once was incredible, it was however soon over as the fleet entered the Sol system. <br>
<br>
“Thanks Dad.” Beka muttered to herself so low that Tyr never even heard it. <br>
<br>
“Rommie. Rommie? Where the hell…” <br>
<br>
“I’m here Dylan.” <br>
<br>
Dylan turned as the doors to Command closed behind the ships Avatar Rommie. <br>
<br>
&quot;Eh, fleet wide.” <br>
<br>
“Aye.” <br>
<br>
“This is Hunt, all ships, Battle Stations.” <br>
<br>
The lighting on Command changed instantly to the dark, eerie place the Andromeda’s crew had seen once too many, but at least this time, it was their choice. <br>
<br>
The fleet entered the system about twenty minutes out from Earth; Beka took them in, the Andromeda leading the pack of supposedly Drago Kazov ships. As the rest of the crew made did some last minute checks and made some final preparation Rommie walked over to Harper and kissed him on the cheek, an action that did not go unnoticed, especially by Dylan. <br>
<br>
“Thank you.” She said. <br>
<br>
“Hey, couldn’t have my Rom Doll feeling left out now could I.” She smiled at the use of a pet name she hadn’t heard for a while. <br>
<br>
Rommie’s new uniform was similar to Dylan’s, while his was all black with the red stripe and all of Harper’s additions, Rommie’s while still black and long sleeved had a V-neck, much shorter than Harper would have liked but he did after all want to live to see Earth freed. The V-neck showed very little skin, the top also had a collar, which ran into the V, it was on the collar where the white patches of the uniform were placed only this time rimmed in blue, the blue also rimmed the collar. While officially Rommie held no rank or special status the patches were far from empty. Inside each was an image, on the left was an image of the Andromeda, well, an XMC, pointing to the right while on the right pointing left was a forcelance, Harper always thought that Rommie was more of a hands on warrior deep down, more like a lancer than a warship so to him at least, the lance made sense. Again on the side of the arms below the shoulders was the new Commonwealth emblem, similar to the original Commonwealth insignia only more stylised with a colour change and the standards of the 50 original member worlds positioned in a circle around it. No red stripes this time but there were blue ones, angled upwards at the cuffs of the sleeves, three on each arm. <br>
<br>
About half way to Earth, Rommie now at the First Officers podium reported something very unusual. <br>
